The paper deals with the problem of finding a correspondence between images and spoken captions, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are often associated with cs.LG (Machine Learning), and it deals with multimodal data, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also mentions data augmentation, which could be relevant to cs.SD (Sound).
